1 (2) The Department shall use revenue from the Fund to pay a nonprofit
2 training entity.
3 (3) Revenue from the Fund may be used only to pay:
4 (i) a nonprofit training entity; and
5 (ii) administrative costs of the Program.
6 (4) The Secretary, or the Secretary’s designee, shall administer the Fund.
7 (5) (i) The Fund is a special, nonlapsing fund that is not subject to §
8 7–302 of the State Finance and Procurement Article.
9 (ii) The State Treasurer shall hold the Fund separately, and the
10 Comptroller shall account for the Fund.
11 (6) The Fund consists of:
12 (i) revenue collected by the Department in the form of donations to
13 the Program;
14 (ii) money appropriated in the State budget to the Fund; and
15 (iii) any other money from any other source accepted for the benefit
16 of the Fund.
17 (7) The State Treasurer shall invest the money of the Fund in the same
18 manner as other State money may be invested.
19 (8) Any interest earnings of the Fund shall be credited to the General Fund
20 of the State.
21 (9) Expenditures from the Fund may be made only in accordance with the
22 State budget.
23 (10) Money expended from the Fund is supplemental to and is not intended
24 to take the place of funding that otherwise would be appropriated for the Program.
25 (g) (1) For the purpose of implementing this section, the Department may
26 accept gifts or grants for donation to the Fund.
27 (2) On or before October 1, 2018, and each October 1 thereafter, the
28 Department shall post and maintain on its website a list containing the names of all
29 persons who have donated to the Fund in the previous year and have authorized the
30 Department to publish their names on its website.

